_refine_special_details          
;
Hydrogen atoms were not found in the difference map, so they were not refined 
in the structure. The methylammonium positions were found in the difference 
map. The C and the N share the same positions in all disordered sites. 
They were refined with EADP and EXYZ. A DFIX command was used to ensure 
chemically  reasonable bond lengths. Hydrogen atoms were not included in the 
methylammonium groups due to the extreme disorder.  
 The reported SumFormula, MoietyFormula, and molecular weight have been updated
to include the twelve methylammonium hydrogens.
 This dataset was collected at 16 KeV, near the absorption edge of Pb. This may
explain the high value of Rint and the differences in residual density.
 The presence of heavy atoms may explain the low precision on the C-C bonds.
 DISP parameters were generated for this wavelength (16 KeV) using WinGX.
;
